FBIS4-7565 "dreeu063__a94037" FBIS-EEU-94-063-A Daily Report 31 Mar 1994 ANNEX Yugoslavia, Kosovo Writers Criticize Milosevic on Human Rights Writers Criticize Milosevic on Human Rights AU3103163094 Tirana ATA in English 1023 GMT 31 Mar 94 -- FOR OFFICIAL USE ONLY AU3103163094 Tirana ATA English BFN [Text] Tirana, March 30 (ATA) -- The committee of the Pen International recently has sent a letter to the Serbian president, Slobodan Milosevic, expressing its concern for the maltreatment of the Albanian writers in Kosova and urging him to stop the violation of the writers' rights there. The imprisonment of Murteza Nura and Shaip Broiri is considered in the letter as an unlawful act because they are being kept in prison for a non-violent activity.
